# Documentation

## Purpose

Keep docs as the source of truth for humans and AI across sprints.

## When It Applies

Any feature, architecture change, API addition, or sprint completion.

## Requirements

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| New API route | `docs/API.md` |
| Architecture decision | `docs/DECISIONS.md` (ADR) |
| New sprint | `docs/TASKS.md`, `docs/ROADMAP.md` |
| Release | `docs/RELEASES.md`, `CHANGELOG.md` |
| New package | `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`, `docs/PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md` |
| Coding convention | `docs/CODING_GUIDE.md` |

- Use templates from `docs/templates/` for new documents.
- Write for AI consumption: explicit constraints, file paths, out-of-scope.
- Keep ROADMAP checkboxes in sync with reality.

## Examples

```
✅ Sprint 2-1 adds @repo/core → updates BACKEND_ARCHITECTURE.md + DECISIONS ADR-003
✅ New /api/users → API.md endpoint section + Zod schema noted
```

## Bad Examples

```
❌ Code merged with zero doc updates
❌ ADR without context, alternatives, or decision rationale
❌ Duplicate info in 5 files without cross-links
```
